stores are spread out,

00:22:37.440 --> 00:22:42.950
you have the home section,
the pro section, music, photo, movie.

00:22:43.330 --> 00:22:44.410
Those are the different zones.

00:22:44.420 --> 00:22:48.860
We sort of see how a consumer
interacts with their computer.

00:22:48.860 --> 00:22:52.630
And so the products that are
related to that are typically

00:22:52.700 --> 00:22:55.200
our most successful products.

00:22:55.350 --> 00:22:59.720
And we also are always looking at
carrying the latest operating system.

00:22:59.720 --> 00:23:03.660
We're not interested in products
that were popular a year ago.

00:23:03.770 --> 00:23:09.120
We want the stuff that is the latest
and greatest and works with the absolute

00:23:09.120 --> 00:23:11.670
brand new systems that we have out there.

00:23:11.730 --> 00:23:15.430
So those are just sort
of our restrictions.

00:23:17.160 --> 00:23:18.880
Packaging.

00:23:18.880 --> 00:23:23.030
We care a lot more about packaging
than any of our competitors.

00:23:23.150 --> 00:23:29.070
If you look in our stores,
we want it to be more of an experience

00:23:29.470 --> 00:23:32.640
than an active selling environment.

00:23:32.640 --> 00:23:38.160
We want the packages to be attractive,
to look good on the shelves,

00:23:38.180 --> 00:23:42.330
to be informative, so that if a customer
picks the product up,

00:23:42.410 --> 00:23:45.120
they can quickly figure out
what the product is about.

00:23:45.920 --> 00:23:50.440
We don't carry jewel cases,
we don't have bulk stacks,

00:23:50.470 --> 00:23:53.820
we don't have POPs,
we don't have end caps.

00:23:53.860 --> 00:23:57.930
We want the products to sit on
the shelves and sell themselves,

00:23:57.990 --> 00:23:59.120
is really what we're looking for.

00:23:59.120 --> 00:24:02.280
So we're not interested
in bells and whistles.

00:24:02.280 --> 00:24:06.420
We want a product to really speak
for itself and its packaging.

00:24:06.530 --> 00:24:11.890
We prefer the smaller boxes,
and I put that in because some people

00:24:11.890 --> 00:24:16.130
get surprised when they've spent
all this time working on a product

00:24:16.210 --> 00:24:18.970
and they come out with this big box.

00:24:19.010 --> 00:24:23.140
Shelf space is a consideration
for all retailers,

00:24:23.140 --> 00:24:26.490
and the smaller box allows
us to carry more merchandise.

00:24:26.650 --> 00:24:29.520
So whenever possible,
we prefer the smaller box.

00:24:29.690 --> 00:24:33.060
It's not that we want to give one
an unfair advantage over another,

00:24:33.060 --> 00:24:36.420
it's that we just have limited
shelf space and we want to be as

00:24:36.560 --> 00:24:39.780
fair and representative to all.

